The course provides the student with a knowledge of the key aspects of practical English phonetics, IPA symbols and phonemic transcription. By engaging in different learning activities, the student will both advance their theoretical knowledge about phonetics and develop their ability to produce and analyse sounds and patterns of sounds characteristic of the English language and to transcribe different texts.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide the student with knowledge of the key aspects of practical English phonetics, IPA symbols and phonemic transcription, and to provide students with an opportunity to practice and improve their pronunciation as well as analyse segmental and suprasegmental aspects of their and their coursemates' speech based on the knowledge acquired during the course.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course, the student will: - be able to analyse English speech on segmental and supra-segmental levels; - be able to analyse and evaluate the strengths and weaknesses of their own English speech;  - in a groupwork setting, have analysed and evaluated the strengths and weaknesses of their coursemates' English speech production and have provided constructive feedback based on the knowledge acquired during the course; - have improved their pronunciation of English; - have the ability to transcribe different texts using phonemic transcription.
